# itemDetails product copy tone

When writing or editing **`itemDetails`** in `projects/**/config.json`, [`scripts/lib/item-details-catalog.mjs`](../../scripts/lib/item-details-catalog.mjs), or story-page “About this item” prose:

## Direction (owner-safe)

Help readers understand **what the item is** — not what it is “worth.” Owners bring beloved toys; avoid copy that sounds like appraisal, downgrade, or collector pricing.

**Lead with:**
- Manufacturer, license, character, era or release window
- Origin (country, brand line, retail channel type)
- Materials, scale, mechanisms, typical features
- How to identify the piece (tags, stamps, model codes, box art)

**Do not lead with or emphasize:**
- Market value, resale, eBay sold prices, USD/AUD ranges
- “Modest / affordable / premium” value judgments
- Buyer demand, collector premiums, “worth more if…”
- Sentimental vs monetary comparisons (e.g. “value exceeds resale”)

`repairDetails` may describe the owner’s story; **`itemDetails` stays factual product context.**

## Tools

- Tone pass: `node scripts/refresh-item-details-tone.mjs`
- Fill from catalog: `node scripts/fill-project-item-details.mjs`
- Sync live HTML prose: `publish-webpage.mjs` or `syncProjectStoryProseHtml` in [`project-story-prose-html.mjs`](../../scripts/lib/project-story-prose-html.mjs)

See also *publish content guards* → `itemDetails` tone section.
